    "rich_text_AGtD9Q": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_bn9hBm": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Entry to Beebe & Beyond Gets You: ",
            "heading_size": "h1",
            "isAnchor": "default",
            "anchorLabel": "",
            "anchorID": ""
          }
        },
        "text_nNWPbc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ul><li>$5 donation to Columbia County Mountain Bike Association, who designed and maintain the singletrack trails </li><li>1 post-ride drink ticket for <a href=\"https://roejanbrewing.com/beer-styles/\" target=\"_blank\">a free beer or cider from our hosts at Roe Jan Brewing Co</a>. </li><li>100% cotton Beebe & Beyond t-shirt </li><li>Flexible registration - You can switch your day (Saturday or Sunday) any time</li><li>Reassurance of riding in a fully insured and NYS DEC permitted event </li><li>All day socializing on bikes on a scenic, shaded route around the border of New York and Massachusetts.</li></ul><h3>Fellow Riders and Pace Groups: </h3><p>Some folks will probably go as fast as they can, especially on the longer routes. But the shorter routes will have a ‘party pace’ 8mph average cluster of riders that will finish with more than 5 hours of riding, plus time enjoyed at the aid station and local landmarks along the route. </p><h3>Local Landmarks: </h3><p>The shorter routes pass by these 3 optional diversions:</p><ol><li>Rodgers Book Barn for browsing shelves of used books in a very charming building</li><li>Beebe Hill Fire Tower for big vistas. The fire tower is accessible via a 1-mile foot trail, and you can leave your bike at the aid station while you walk </li><li>The author Edna St. Vincent Millay's residence “Steepletop”</li></ol><p></p><h3>Post-Ride Fun: </h3><p>On a hot summer afternoon after a very hilly bicycle ride, head indoors at Roe Jan Brewing to the air conditioned dining room and order off of their full menu. Downstairs at the covered patio there are the same beers and ciders with a limited food menu. </p><p>Stick around until the evening and you will catch the live music crowd. The brewery has a musicians calendar booked months in advance. Saturday from 7-9pm the performer will be <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DGbeE3EJBah/\" target=\"_blank\">Mark Phillips and his band Hot Chestnut</a> performing pure classic jazz and Sunday from 5-7pm the performer will be <a href=\"http://www.stumpsongs.com/\" target=\"_blank\">the Bob Stump Band</a> performing lively americana. </p>"
          }
        },
